From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: kSTEP <kstep@kstep.dev>
Date: Sat, 15 Mar 2026 05:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] sched/deadline: Fix PELT sync in switched_to_dl() under
 CONFIG_SCHED_PROXY_EXEC

switched_to_dl() uses rq->donor to decide whether to call
update_dl_rq_load_avg().  Under CONFIG_SCHED_PROXY_EXEC, rq->donor
(scheduling context) can differ from rq->curr (execution context)
during proxy execution.  When the currently executing task has its
policy changed to SCHED_DEADLINE and it is not the donor, the PELT
avg_dl.last_update_time is not synchronised, producing a utilisation
spike on the subsequent accounting update—the same class of bug fixed
for RT in commit fecfcbc288e9 ("sched/rt: Fix RT utilization tracking
during policy change").

Use task_current(rq, p) (checks rq->curr) instead of the donor
comparison, mirroring the pattern established in switched_to_rt().
When p is the currently executing task, update PELT and return early;
otherwise fall through to the push/preempt logic.

Fixes: af0c8b2bf67b ("sched: Rework switched_to_dl()")
Signed-off-by: kSTEP <kstep@kstep.dev>
---
 kernel/sched/deadline.c | 15 ++++++++-------
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/deadline.c b/kernel/sched/deadline.c
index eca76669c..b7e9f3c12 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/deadline.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/deadline.c
@@ -3293,16 +3293,17 @@ static void switched_to_dl(struct rq *rq, struct task_struct *p)
 		return;
 	}
 
-	if (rq->donor != p) {
-		if (p->nr_cpus_allowed > 1 && rq->dl.overloaded)
-			deadline_queue_push_tasks(rq);
-		if (dl_task(rq->donor))
-			wakeup_preempt_dl(rq, p, 0);
-		else
-			resched_curr(rq);
-	} else {
+	if (task_current(rq, p)) {
 		update_dl_rq_load_avg(rq_clock_pelt(rq), rq, 0);
+		return;
 	}
+
+	if (p->nr_cpus_allowed > 1 && rq->dl.overloaded)
+		deadline_queue_push_tasks(rq);
+	if (dl_task(rq->donor))
+		wakeup_preempt_dl(rq, p, 0);
+	else
+		resched_curr(rq);
 }
 
 static u64 get_prio_dl(struct rq *rq, struct task_struct *p)
